   "source": [
    "# Notebook 02: Preprocesamiento y Análisis del Dataset Landslide4Sense\n",
    "**Proyecto de Maestría:** Detección de Deslizamientos con IA\n",
    | Universidad EAFIT\n",
    "\n",
    "Este notebook automatiza la carga manual, descompresión y visualización multiespectral de los datos en Google Colab."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 1. Preparación del Entorno\n",
    "Instalamos utilidades para archivos comprimidos y cargamos librerías de procesamiento."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "!apt-get install p7zip-full -y  # Soporte para .7z\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import h5py\n",
    "import zipfile\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "from pathlib import Path\n",
    "from google.colab import files\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"✓ Entorno listo.\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 2. Gestión del Dataset (Carga y Descompresión)\n",
    "Aquí subimos el archivo `landslide4sense.zip` (o .7z) y configuramos las rutas dinámicas para evitar el error de '0 muestras'."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "# 2.1 Subida manual\n",
    "path_archivo = '/content/landslide4sense.zip' # Cambiar a .7z si es el caso\n",
    "\n",
    "if not os.path.exists(path_archivo):\n",
    "    print(\"Por favor, sube tu archivo comprimido:\")\n",
    "    uploaded = files.upload()\n",
    "    # Si se subió con otro nombre, lo renombramos para el script\n",
    "    nombre_subido = list(uploaded.keys())[0]\n",
    "    if nombre_subido != 'landslide4sense.zip':\n",
    "        os.rename(nombre_subido, 'landslide4sense.zip')\n",
    "        path_archivo = '/content/landslide4sense.zip'\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2.2 Descompresión\n",
    "print(\"Descomprimiendo dataset...\")\n",
    "if path_archivo.endswith('.7z'):\n",
    "    !7z x {path_archivo} -o/content/dataset_temp -y > /dev/null\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    with zipfile.ZipFile(path_archivo, 'r') as zip_ref:\n",
    "        zip_ref.extractall('/content/dataset_temp')\n",
    "\n",
    "# 2.3 Localización de Carpetas (Estructura detectada en imagen)\n",
    "detector = list(Path('/content/dataset_temp').glob('**/TrainData/img'))\n",
    "\n",
    "if detector:\n",
    "    DATA_ROOT = detector[0].parent.parent\n",
    "    print(f\"\\n✅ ¡Ruta detectada exitosamente!\")\n",
    "    print(f\"Raíz de datos: {DATA_ROOT}\")\n",
    "    \n",
    "    img_list = sorted(list((DATA_ROOT / \"img\").glob(\"*.h5\")))\n",
    "    mask_list = sorted(list((DATA_ROOT / \"mask\").glob(\"*.h5\")))\n",
    "    print(f\"Muestras de entrenamiento: {len(img_list)}\")\n",
    "else:\n",
    "    print(\"❌ No se encontró la estructura TrainData/img. Revisa el contenido:\")\n",
    "    !ls -R /content/dataset_temp | head -n 15"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## 3. Análisis de Datos H5 (Sentinel-2 + DEM + Slope)\n",
    "Exploramos las 14 bandas disponibles: 1-12 (Sentinel-2), 13 (Slope), 14 (DEM)."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def read_sample(path):\n",
    "    with h5py.File(path, 'r') as f:\n",
    "        # El dataset suele llamarse 'img' o 'mask', usamos el primer key\n",
    "        return np.array(f[list(f.keys())[0]])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualizar una muestra\n",
    "idx = np.random.randint(0, len(img_list))\n",
    "img = read_sample(img_list[idx])\n",
    "mask = read_sample(mask_list[idx])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Combinación RGB: B4(Red)=3, B3(Green)=2, B2(Blue)=1\n",
    "rgb = img[:, :, [3, 2, 1]]\n",
    "rgb = (rgb - rgb.min()) / (rgb.max() - rgb.min() + 1e-8)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Información Topográfica: Slope (Banda 13) y DEM (Banda 14)\n",
    "slope = img[:, :, 12]\n",
    "dem = img[:, :, 13]\n",
    "\n",
    "fig, axes = plt.subplots(1, 4, figsize=(20, 5))\n",
    "axes[0].imshow(rgb); axes[0].set_title(\"Sentinel-2 RGB\"); axes[0].axis('off')\n",
    "axes[1].imshow(slope, cmap='terrain'); axes[1].set_title(\"Pendiente (Slope)\"); axes[1].axis('off')\n",
    "axes[2].imshow(dem, cmap='gist_earth'); axes[2].set_title(\"Elevación (DEM)\"); axes[2].axis('off')\n",
    "axes[3].imshow(mask, cmap='inferno'); axes[3].set_title(\"Máscara (Deslizamiento)\"); axes[3].axis('off')\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()\n",
    "print(f\"Dimensiones de la muestra: {img.shape}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
